Hello, How am I, I am extremely well thank you. How old am I, I am in my late 50s. My name is Tony Millner.

 The reason I have come for a sight test today is because I've noticed my distance vision is no longer as good as it was, and I don't have any glasses for my distance vision. I do however wear glasses for reading.

The reason I have come for a sight test today is because I've noticed my distance vision is no longer as good as it was, and I don't have any glasses for my distance vision. I do however wear glasses for reading. I've been wearing reading glasses for the past 15 years and I can see well with them. I'm not really having any other visual problems!

 My last eye test was on 26/10/2019, but I think my reading glasses are a little older, I can't quite remember.

 My last eye test was on 26/10/2019, but I think my reading glasses are a little older, I can't quite remember. My glasses could be 5 years old now, I'm not entirely sure exactly.

 For the past year now I've been getting dull headaches, on and off, on the side of my head, around once a week, when doing computer work or reading for long periods of time. Luckily, I don't get any eyestrain but the headaches are getting annoying.

 I don't get any double vision or floaters but for several years I've been getting flashes in my vision every night, not sure if its happening in both eyes or just one. Other than that I haven't noticed anything else. The flashing lights happen when I get up in the night to go to the loo, they just last a second or two.

 I have had problems with my eyes in the past, about 30 years ago I had a cyst removed. When I was discharged from the hospital, I was prescribed lid scrubs for my blepharitis. That was the only time I went to an eye hospital.

 My family don't have any health problems, like diabetes or high blood pressure. In my family, my dad had cataracts.

My family don't have any health problems, like diabetes or high blood pressure. In my family, my dad had cataracts. The only eye problem in my family has been cataract. 

 My general health is good. I don't have diabetes but I am genetically predisposed to type 2 diabetes, and my last medical exam was 2 months ago to get my blood sugar levels checked.

I take vitamin D and cod liver oil supplements but no medication like pills or tablets. Around May/ June time I may take antihistamines and sometimes steroid drops if my hayfever really flares up. I don't smoke since I know it's damaging to my health.

 For a living, work, I am a secondary school teacher. I teach biology.

For a living, work, I am a secondary school teacher. I teach biology. I really enjoy teaching. I spend about 6 hours a day looking at my computer screen since I'm a teacher. I also spend too long on my mobile phone, I would say about 2 hours a day.
